            <fr:title text="Inner Product">Inner Product</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An inner product on a <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0099">vector space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> over a field <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> (either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>) is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \langle  \cdot , \cdot  \rangle : X \times  X \rightarrow  K]]></fr:tex> satisfying the following properties for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y, z \in  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha , \beta  \in  K]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \langle  \alpha  x + \beta  y, z \rangle  = \alpha  \langle  x, z \rangle  + \beta  \langle  y, z \rangle ]]></fr:tex> (linearity in first argument)</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \langle  x, y \rangle  = \overline {\langle  y, x \rangle }]]></fr:tex> (conjugate symmetry)</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \langle  x, x \rangle  \geq  0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \langle  x, x \rangle  = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = 0]]></fr:tex> (positive definiteness)</fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>An inner product induces a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002S.xml" addr="FA-002S" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> via <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ |x| = \sqrt {\langle  x, x \rangle }]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002M.xml" addr="FA-002M" title="Inner Product">inner product space</fr:link> can be completed to form a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002J.xml" addr="FA-002J" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1181</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002K</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002K.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Normed Space">Normed Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A normed space is a <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0099">vector space</fr:link> equipped with a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002S.xml" addr="FA-002S" title="Norm">norm</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a vector space over the field <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> (either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>). A norm on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left | \cdot  \right |: X \rightarrow  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> satisfying the following properties for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y \in  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  K]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left | x \right | \geq  0]]></fr:tex> (non-negativity)</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left | x \right | = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = 0]]></fr:tex> (positive definiteness)</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left | \alpha  x \right | = |\alpha | \cdot  |x|]]></fr:tex> (homogeneity)</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \left | x + y \right | \leq  |x| + |y|]]></fr:tex> (triangle inequality)</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1183</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003F</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003F.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Operator Norm">Operator Norm</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The operator norm is a type of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002S.xml" addr="FA-002S" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> defined for <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002G.xml" addr="FA-002G" title="Bounded Linear Operator">bounded linear operators</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>For a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002G.xml" addr="FA-002G" title="Bounded Linear Operator">bounded linear operator</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T: X \rightarrow  Y]]></fr:tex> between <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002K.xml" addr="FA-002K" title="Normed Space">normed spaces</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, the operator norm is defined as:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{||T|| = \sup _{x \neq  0} \frac {||Tx||_Y}{||x||_X} = \sup _{||x||_X=1} ||Tx||_Y}]]></fr:tex>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>This norm measures the maximum "stretching factor" of the operator, i.e., how much the operator can amplify the length of a unit vector.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Key properties:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>A linear operator is <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0131">bounded</fr:link> if and only if it has a finite operator norm</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For operators <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ ||S \circ  T|| \leq  ||S|| \cdot  ||T||]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
  <fr:li>The set of bounded linear operators from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B(X,Y)]]></fr:tex>, forms a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002I.xml" addr="FA-002I" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link> when equipped with the operator norm</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1185</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003G</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003G.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Sup Norm">Sup Norm</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The supremum norm (or sup norm) is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002S.xml" addr="FA-002S" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> defined for bounded functions. For a bounded function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f: X \rightarrow  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f: X \rightarrow  \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, the sup norm is defined as:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{||f||_\infty  = \sup _{x \in  X} |f(x)|}]]></fr:tex>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>This norm measures the maximum absolute value that the function takes over its domain.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In the context of the <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0132">space of continuous functions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C(X)]]></fr:tex> on a compact space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the sup norm makes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C(X)]]></fr:tex> into a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002I.xml" addr="FA-002I" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>The sup norm is also used to define the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^\infty ]]></fr:tex> space, which consists of essentially bounded <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003D.xml" addr="FA-003D" title="Measurable Function">measurable functions</fr:link>, with the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003E.xml" addr="FA-003E" title="Essential Supremum">essential supremum</fr:link> replacing the exact supremum.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
